BLACK MESA OFFICES, WELCOME TO CHAOS


Good news. We're in the offices. Finally. Desks, conference rooms, coffee machines that no one will turn on again, and a pleasant feeling that we've finally arrived somewhere.

Better news. Zap Gun and Buzzsaw are back with us. Our faithful friends, who have never let us down, except for those three times. Which means Mental is already somewhere nearby. Or maybe not here. His soldiers are nowhere to be seen, but the ammo is lying right on the floor, like someone handing out bonuses before leaving. Strange, huh? The enemy didn't show up, but left the ammo behind. Either they're very generous, or we'll soon have a reason to use it.

Bad news. H.E.C.U. is already here. Not "arriving soon", not "deploying forces". They've already taken over the upper floors of the offices. The very floors we need to get through to get out of this story.

The scenario is familiar. The Marines have arrived to carry out orders: clear out everything that moves and ask no questions. For them, we're either a surviving scientist (execution), an alien spy (execution), or simply a witness (also execution). There aren't many options. They've taken up positions upstairs, blocked the stairwells, set up firing points. Now they feel in control. They're wrong.

No mental breakdown. For now. But the bullets aren't just lying around. So either he's already passed through here and left a trace, or he's getting ready.

Let's go quietly. And may Zap Gun not let us down today.